tomboy-ng (0.41-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Release of new version
  * Updates to PDF maker, especially Chinese capabilities. User can
    select font.
  * Fix to github sync handling transit net failures better.
  * Sort recover notes.
  * Warn Gnome and Qt6 users of Systray Issues.
  * AppImage, Linux
  * Remove dependency on wmctrl, Linux.
  * Add multiselect and right click menu to Search Right Click, inc 2
    later fixes.
  * A fix for bug triggered when several notes are needing a save at
    quit time.
  * A fix for Debian reproducibly issue.
  * Repackage -1 for arm64 only because of glibc issue
  * Please see github for change details.

 -- David Bannon <tomboy-ng@bannons.id.au>  Wed, 11 Dec 2024 22:32:47 +1100

tomboy-ng (0.40-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  *  Release of new version.
  * Revised Bullet control system.
  * Revised Color setting system for Qt5 and Qt6.
  * Tab key now indents paragraph, not compatible with old Tomboy.
    Subject to revision.
  * Revised PDF export, embedded fonts.
  * Draft "file link" capability. Just type file://Path_to_a_file, use
    the Right Click Menu or Alt-F or Alt-D to insert file or directory
    link interactivly. Will open any file your systems knows how to
    open.
  * Support for openssl 3.0 (compile with fpc323, require dev pkg on
    Debian).
  * Better debug capability when using GitHub Sync.
  * Fix to ensure Gnome is happy with Qt5/6 using -platform xcb.
  * Rename --kde-leftclick to --allow-leftclick because now useful under
    Gnome too.
  * Updates to man page and command line help.
  * Closes: #1061429 - On Wayland Systems, must use xcb.
  * Please see github for further change details.

 -- David Bannon <tomboy-ng@bannons.id.au>  Sat, 29 Jun 2024 16:44:10 +1000

